  abstract = {Future skills are regarded as a solution for current societal and global challenges. In the German political discourse, the concept has been introduced without a proper analysis and critical discussion of prior approaches and evidence of the concept and its impact on adult outcomes. In this paper I briefly introduce the historical discourse on future skills of the last 20 years. Based on existing systematic literature reviews and evidence syntheses I summarise the current state-of-the art of research and identify 9 fundamental problems of the concept and funding of future skill initiatives. Among others, the missing connection and systematisation regarding earlier approaches, the missing evidence of effects of future skills on adult outcomes and the lack of measurement approaches are identified as important shortcomings for the promotion of future skills. As an alternative approach I discuss the funding of transfer research within and outside of a domain of expertise.},
